  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening pastoralist communities&#x2019; resilience to climate change in Samburu county</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishment of community governance structures linked to devolved structures - WCCPC, Community Conversation Platforms, Climate Champions
- Capacity building of community structures on legislation, planning and budgeting cycle, social accountability
- Engagement with county government on policy and legislation on climate change financing and adaptation.
- Facilitate community participation and voice especially  women and youth
- Learning through impelementation</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased capacity of communities to meaningfully participate in County Planning and Budgeting for Climate Change Adaptation 
Climate change knowledge and learning integrated into programme management 
Improved capacity  of community based institutions in sustainable rangeland management and livelihoods diversification 
Improved policy environment for sustainable rangeland management, livestock production and access to climate information services  at the county level</narrative>
  </description>
